						               													<description>This is the WW2 edition of the Ambush miniature rules series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a complete game, including fully integrated infantry and armour rules that can be played in a reasonable time. Use of an hex grid recommended for smoother play.&amp;#10;Smaller tables can be played in as little as 45 minutes.&amp;#10;Infantry three stand units represent platoons or full companies and they do play their proper role; like in reality mighty tanks are of little use unless properly supported. This is effectively enforced by simply awarding full objective values only when infantry is placed over them.&amp;#10;The game does not feature common alternate turns, instead HQ issue orders accordingly to random initiative dice (d6); this means that HQ Ally1 may activate, then HQ Axis1, then HQ Ally2, etc.   &amp;#10;The rules feature 1:144 miniature pictures and are probably best from 1:200 to 1:144.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Because of its design and the use of an hex grid by default, this game has been pointed as a bridge between wargames and boardgames.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: this is a rules book only, an hex grid, a dozen d6, 1 d20 dice and miniatures or custom built counters required to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
